article.headline: Troy 115, Arkansas-Fort Smith 76
article.story: STATESBORO, Ga. -- Brandon Hazzard scored 27 points to lead Troy in a 115-76 victory over Arkansas-Fort Smith in the Legends Classic on Friday night. Hazzard shot 10-for-18 from the field and hit four 3-pointers for the Trojans (3-2). Antywan Jones, Yamene Coleman, Michael Vogler and Richard Delk also chipped in with 15 points each. Troy shot 46.3 percent (19-for-41) in the first half to jump out to a 51-37 halftime lead. In the second half, Vogler nailed a 3-pointer that capped a 21-3 run, giving the Trojans a 72-47 lead with 14:08 remaining. Troy would take its largest lead of the game after Bernard Toombs' dunk with 1:38 left made the score 115-71. The Lions (1-3) were led in scoring by Josh Simmons, who scored 24 points and grabbed eight rebounds. Jalynn Mitchell added 18 points. The Lions were outrebounded 47-36, and committed 24 turnovers.
